Step 1: Create Folder + Files
Folder:
Docker-Java
📄 Dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk
WORKDIR /app
COPY . /app
RUN javac Calc.java
CMD ["java", "Calc"]

 Used to build and run Java program inside container

📄 Calc.java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Calc {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.print("Enter two numbers: ");
    int a = sc.nextInt();
    int b = sc.nextInt();
    System.out.println("Sum = " + (a + b));
    sc.close();
  }
}

Simple program to add two numbers

 Step 2: Build Docker Image
docker build -t java-app .

 Creates Docker image from Dockerfile

 Step 3: Login to Docker Hub
docker login -u yourusername
 Authenticate using username + access token
 Step 4: Tag the Image
docker tag java-app yourusername/java-app:v1
Assigns repository name and version

 Step 5: Push Image to Docker Hub
docker push yourusername/java-app:v1

 Uploads image to Docker Hub

 Step 6: Run the Program
docker run -it yourusername/java-app:v1

Runs container and shows calculator output

 Final Output Example
Enter two numbers:
5 3
Sum = 8
 Result

Successfully built, tagged, pushed Docker image and executed Java calculator program
